#: ../../manual/game_engine/camera/stereo.rst:23
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Specifies the way in which the left-eye image and the right-eye image pixels "
"are put together during rendering. This must be selected according to the "
"type of apparatus available to display the appropriate images to the "
"viewer's eyes."
msgstr ""
"Spécifie la manière avec laquelle les pixels de l'image de l’œil gauche et "
"celle de l’œil droit sont mis ensemble pendant le rendu. Ceci doit être "
"sélectionné selon le type d'appareil disponible pour afficher les images "
"appropriées. "

#: ../../manual/game_engine/camera/stereo.rst:29
msgid "Anaglyph"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/game_engine/camera/stereo.rst:28
msgid ""
"One frame is displayed with both images color encoded with red-blue filters. "
"This mode only requires `glasses with color filters <https://en.wikipedia."
"org/wiki/Stereoscopy#Color_anaglyph_systems>`__, there are no special "
"requirements for the display screen and GPU."
msgstr ""
"Une images est affichée avec les couleurs des deux images encodées avec des "
"filtres rouge-bleu. Ce mode exige seulement des `verres avec des filtres "
"couleur <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/"
"Stereoscopy#Color_anaglyph_systems>`__, il n'y a pas d'exigences "
"particulières pour l'écran d'affichage et le GPU. "

#: ../../manual/game_engine/camera/stereo.rst:33
msgid "Quad Buffer"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/game_engine/camera/stereo.rst:32
msgid ""
"Uses double buffering with a buffer for each eye, totaling four buffers "
"(Left Front, Left Back, Right Front and Right Back), allowing to swap the "
"buffers for both eyes in sync. See `Quad Buffering <https://en.wikipedia.org/"
"wiki/Quad_buffering>`__ for more information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/game_engine/camera/stereo.rst:35
msgid "Side by Side"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/game_engine/camera/stereo.rst:36
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Lines are displayed one after the other, so providing the two images in two "
"frames side by side."
msgstr ""
"Les images sont affichées l'une après l'autre, fournissant les deux images "
"dans deux cadres côte à côte."

#: ../../manual/game_engine/camera/stereo.rst:37
msgid "Above-Below"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/game_engine/camera/stereo.rst:38
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Frames are displayed one after the other, so providing the two images in two "
"frames, one above the other."
msgstr ""
"Les images sont affichées l'une après l'autre, fournissant les deux images "
"dans deux cadres, l'un au dessus de l'autre."

#: ../../manual/game_engine/camera/stereo.rst:39
msgid "Interlaced"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/game_engine/camera/stereo.rst:40
msgid ""
"One frame is displayed with the two images on alternate lines of the display."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/game_engine/camera/stereo.rst:42
msgid "Vinterlaced"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/game_engine/camera/stereo.rst:42
msgid ""
"One frame is displayed with both images displayed on alternate columns of "
"the display. This works with some 'autostereo displays'."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/game_engine/camera/stereo.rst:46
msgid "3D Tv Top-Bottom"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/game_engine/camera/stereo.rst:45
msgid ""
"One frame displays the left image above and the right image below. The "
"images are squashed vertically to fit. This mode is designed for passive 3D "
"TV."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/game_engine/camera/stereo.rst:52
msgid "Eye Separation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/game_engine/camera/stereo.rst:49
msgid ""
"This value is extremely important. It determines how far apart the two image-"
"capturing cameras are, and thus how \"deep\" the scene appears. Too small a "
"value and the image appears flat; too high a value can result in headaches "
"and eye strain. The ideal value mimics the separation of the viewer's two "
"eyes."
msgstr ""
